updates.title: Meta's chief AI scientist Yann LeCun is reportedly leaving to start his own AI startup focused on world models, marking a significant departure from one of the industry's most influential research leaders.

ElevenLabs launches new AI voice marketplace allowing brands to license AI-replicated voices of famous figures for advertisements and content, expanding commercial applications of synthetic voice technology.
Google Photos introduces conversational AI editing for iPhone users, allowing them to make image edits by typing or verbally describing changes they want to make.

AI customer service startup Wonderful raises massive $100M Series A led by Index Ventures to deploy AI agents for front-line customer support, while coding platform Lovable approaches 8 million users.
Industry veterans share insights on AI startup product-market fit challenges while analysts question whether Wall Street is losing faith in AI investments after recent tech stock volatility.
